00:04:18.300 --> 00:04:19.800
So in this lecture today,

00:04:19.800 --> 00:04:20.820
we're gonna be talking about

00:04:20.820 --> 00:04:23.490
some general causal forces

00:04:23.490 --> 00:04:24.600
which made it likely

00:04:24.600 --> 00:04:27.150
that there would be
states coming into being

00:04:27.150 --> 00:04:29.640
in Eastern Europe around the year 1000.

00:04:29.640 --> 00:04:31.530
And those general causal forces

00:04:31.530 --> 00:04:34.200
are things like Christianity,

00:04:34.200 --> 00:04:37.200
and what Christianity could do for people,

00:04:37.200 --> 00:04:39.093
for rulers and for others.

00:04:40.200 --> 00:04:42.090
Secondly, the fact that Christianity

00:04:42.090 --> 00:04:43.860
was not a singularity,

00:04:43.860 --> 00:04:45.630
but Christianity was a plurality.

00:04:45.630 --> 00:04:48.060
There were two versions of Christianity

00:04:48.060 --> 00:04:49.050
that were emerging.

00:04:49.050 --> 00:04:50.490
From our point of view,

00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:52.993
a Western version and a Southern version,

00:04:52.993 --> 00:04:55.530
a Frankish version and
a Byzantine version.

00:04:55.530 --> 00:04:57.210
And those two versions of Christianity,

00:04:57.210 --> 00:04:58.710
it wasn't their theological differences

00:04:58.710 --> 00:04:59.543
that mattered so much.

00:04:59.543 --> 00:05:01.080
It was that they were represented

00:05:01.080 --> 00:05:03.420
by two strong political units

00:05:03.420 --> 00:05:06.120
that were pushing outward imperially

00:05:06.120 --> 00:05:08.520
into our region,

00:05:08.520 --> 00:05:11.070
in competition with one another.

00:05:11.070 --> 00:05:13.113
In competition with one another.

00:05:13.950 --> 00:05:15.480
And then underlying all this

00:05:15.480 --> 00:05:18.000
is the basic economic status

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:19.470
of the place we're talking about,

00:05:19.470 --> 00:05:22.350
where nomads are still coming and going,

00:05:22.350 --> 00:05:25.950
where slavery is still very prominent.

00:05:25.950 --> 00:05:27.990
And when you think of what statehood does

00:05:27.990 --> 00:05:30.060
for people, one of the things

00:05:30.060 --> 00:05:31.077
that statehood does for people,

00:05:31.077 --> 00:05:33.210
and this is not just
true in Eastern Europe,

00:05:33.210 --> 00:05:35.280
this is a sort of general characterization

00:05:35.280 --> 00:05:36.540
of what a state is,

00:05:36.540 --> 00:05:39.330
statehood protects the people

00:05:39.330 --> 00:05:40.950
that the state recognizes

00:05:40.950 --> 00:05:42.963
from being enslaved by other people.

00:05:46.244 --> 00:05:49.020
So the basic economics

00:05:49.020 --> 00:05:51.960
of the globalization that
we're in at this point,

00:05:51.960 --> 00:05:54.480
circa 800, 900, 1000,

00:05:54.480 --> 00:05:57.270
is a globalization of a slave trade,

00:05:57.270 --> 00:05:59.460
in which the human beings
of our part of the world

00:05:59.460 --> 00:06:02.220
are being shipped, very
far distances sometimes,

00:06:02.220 --> 00:06:03.930
in order to be enslaved.

00:06:03.930 --> 00:06:05.550
That is a form of global economics.

00:06:05.550 --> 00:06:07.860
It persists and expands and continues

00:06:07.860 --> 00:06:09.090
well beyond our region,

00:06:09.090 --> 00:06:10.500
well beyond this time.

00:06:10.500 --> 00:06:13.560
What a state can do is put
a stop to that locally.

00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:16.308
A state can say, "We recognize you.

00:06:16.308 --> 00:06:17.617
"We have the coercive means to make sure

00:06:17.617 --> 00:06:19.387
"that you will not be sold into slavery.

00:06:19.387 --> 00:06:22.297
"We also have the
coercive means to tax you.

00:06:22.297 --> 00:06:25.297
"So we prefer," making
a very long story short,

00:06:25.297 --> 00:06:27.847
"We prefer that you stay
here and work the land,

00:06:27.847 --> 00:06:29.557
"and we tax you,

00:06:29.557 --> 00:06:31.777
"rather than we capture you

00:06:31.777 --> 00:06:33.240
