A lotta the territory
of Russia is inhabited

00:31:44.010 --> 00:31:45.873
by people who are Muslim.

00:31:47.220 --> 00:31:48.930
When I was in Ukraine last week,

00:31:48.930 --> 00:31:52.280
I was talking to a woman who had,

00:31:52.280 --> 00:31:54.390
in Chernihiv oblast, who
had five Russian soldiers

00:31:54.390 --> 00:31:55.860
in her basement.

00:31:55.860 --> 00:31:58.530
And, of course, none of them
were from European Russia.

00:31:58.530 --> 00:32:01.020
And two of them, I think, were Muslims.

00:32:01.020 --> 00:32:02.220
That's Russia, right?

00:32:02.220 --> 00:32:04.440
Russia has been a Muslim country

00:32:04.440 --> 00:32:06.630
from the get-go, among other things.

00:32:06.630 --> 00:32:08.850
But some of the Bulgars, okay,

00:32:08.850 --> 00:32:10.360
some of the Bulgars migrate

00:32:12.254 --> 00:32:14.340
and come to dominate part of the Balkans.

00:32:14.340 --> 00:32:17.100
And they seem to convert to Christianity

00:32:17.100 --> 00:32:18.570
around the year 865.

00:32:18.570 --> 00:32:21.630
And that's the prehistory
of the Bulgarian nation

00:32:21.630 --> 00:32:23.700
that we know and love today.

00:32:23.700 --> 00:32:27.420
And the Bulgarian found a state

00:32:27.420 --> 00:32:29.760
which is Orthodox,

00:32:29.760 --> 00:32:31.350
Eastern Christian, that is,

00:32:31.350 --> 00:32:33.870
but which is in rivalry with Byzantium.

00:32:33.870 --> 00:32:36.510
And that's a very important model, right?

00:32:36.510 --> 00:32:39.750
That you can be Orthodox and Christian,

00:32:39.750 --> 00:32:41.880
but not be actually part

00:32:41.880 --> 00:32:44.640
of the Byzantine Empire.

00:32:44.640 --> 00:32:46.080
That's a model of statehood.

00:32:46.080 --> 00:32:47.670
Very important, right?

00:32:47.670 --> 00:32:49.140
The Bulgarian get there first.

00:32:49.140 --> 00:32:50.940
And part of the way they get there

00:32:50.940 --> 00:32:54.150
is that they use the legacy
of Cyril and Methodius.

00:32:54.150 --> 00:32:55.830
They use Old Church Slavonic.

00:32:55.830 --> 00:32:58.630
They develop, you know, a
slightly national version

00:32:59.494 --> 00:33:01.350
of Eastern Christianity,

00:33:01.350 --> 00:33:05.070
but they're also creating
a model of statehood.

00:33:05.070 --> 00:33:06.483
Okay, by the way,

00:33:08.370 --> 00:33:09.930
you've probably been
wondering like, you know,

00:33:09.930 --> 00:33:11.760
the Russian president's name is Vladimir,

00:33:11.760 --> 00:33:13.470
and the Ukrainian president's
name is Volodymyr.

00:33:13.470 --> 00:33:15.360
So like is Volodymyr a Ukrainian name

00:33:15.360 --> 00:33:17.280
or is it a Russian name?

00:33:17.280 --> 00:33:19.710
It's a Bulgarian name. (laughs)

00:33:19.710 --> 00:33:21.360
It's a Bulgarian name.

00:33:21.360 --> 00:33:23.400
The Volodymyr who's gonna
convert to Christianity

00:33:23.400 --> 00:33:24.450
at the end of this lecture,

00:33:24.450 --> 00:33:27.060
his name was actually a Bulgarian name.

00:33:27.060 --> 00:33:29.700
It's a cultural borrowing from Bulgaria.

00:33:29.700 --> 00:33:31.350
Copying is really important.

00:33:31.350 --> 00:33:32.790
It's much more important than we think.

00:33:32.790 --> 00:33:35.250
Okay, this brings us to the special case

00:33:35.250 --> 00:33:36.870
that we're gonna land on,

00:33:36.870 --> 00:33:38.820
which is the case of the Rus'.

00:33:38.820 --> 00:33:40.560
And when we talk about the Rus'

00:33:40.560 --> 00:33:42.240
and the creation of Kyivan Rus',

00:33:42.240 --> 00:33:45.210
we need to now know who
the local competitors

00:33:45.210 --> 00:33:46.410
for power are.

00:33:46.410 --> 00:33:48.480
The local competitors for power

00:33:48.480 --> 00:33:50.910
in the 8th, 9th and 10th century here

00:33:50.910 --> 00:33:53.910
are the Rus', who we've
talked about a little bit,

00:33:53.910 --> 00:33:55.620
these Scandinavian slavers who come down

00:33:55.620 --> 00:33:59.126
from the Baltic Sea, and the Khazars.

00:33:59.126 --> 00:34:01.412
The Khazars are already present,

00:34:01.412 --> 00:34:04.173
and the Rus' are on their way down.

00:34:07.230 --> 00:34:09.270
So let's talk first about the Rus',

00:34:09.270 --> 00:34:10.930
and then let's talk about the Khazars.

00:34:10.930 --> 00:34:14.310
Okay, so some of you have
asked me about names,

00:34:14.310 --> 00:34:16.260
and it is very, I mean,

00:34:16.260 --> 00:34:17.340
names are very powerful.

00:34:17.340 --> 00:34:19.830
What we name things does
have a certain power,

00:34:19.830 --> 00:34:21.840
and there's a tendency to say

00:34:21.840 --> 00:34:23.160
what something is named now,

00:34:23.160 --> 00:34:26.340
it must reveal something
essential about it.

00:34:26.340 --> 00:34:27.600
And, you know, we all have names

00:34:27.600 --> 00:34:29.100
and like we're called by our names,

00:34:29.100 --> 00:34:31.233
and it runs very deep.

00:34:32.130 --> 00:34:34.230
But one has to be a
little careful about this.

00:34:34.230 --> 00:34:36.810
So like America is called America,

00:34:36.810 --> 00:34:40.480
but we're not all Italian mapmakers

00:34:43.668 --> 00:34:45.180
and so on and so on and so on, right?

00:34:45.180 --> 00:34:48.273
But we still unproblematically
call ourselves America.

00:34:49.410 --> 00:34:52.440
Rossiya, Russia is called Russia

00:34:52.440 --> 00:34:54.177
as a reference to Rus',

00:34:55.320 --> 00:34:57.840
but Rus' is itself the
name of a Scandinavian,

00:34:57.840 --> 00:34:59.700
probably a Scandinavian trading company.

00:34:59.700 --> 00:35:01.743
In any event, a group of Vikings.

00:35:02.820 --> 00:35:04.800
So, and the reason they were called Rus',

00:35:04.800 --> 00:35:05.970
no one is quite sure.

00:35:05.970 --> 00:35:07.830
It's close to a Finnish word

00:35:07.830 --> 00:35:09.513
which means rudder.

00:35:11.588 --> 00:35:13.050
So our best guess is that modern Russia

00:35:13.050 --> 00:35:14.760
is named after an old Finnish word

00:35:14.760 --> 00:35:16.830
for our rudder, right?

00:35:16.830 --> 00:35:18.120
But that doesn't mean that the Russians

00:35:18.120 --> 00:35:21.300
are actually medieval Finnish rudders.

00:35:21.300 --> 00:35:24.240
So the name that something has now

00:35:24.240 --> 00:35:25.260
and like working it back

00:35:25.260 --> 00:35:28.260
doesn't actually have any
magical quality, right?

00:35:28.260 --> 00:35:30.540
So, you know, why Belarus
is called Belarus,

00:35:30.540 --> 00:35:32.370
or Ukraine is called
Ukraine, is interesting,

00:35:32.370 --> 00:35:35.760
but it doesn't necessarily
reveal anything essential

00:35:35.760 --> 00:35:36.990
about the country.

00:35:36.990 --> 00:35:37.823
Okay.

00:35:39.840 --> 00:35:40.673
Right.

00:35:40.673 --> 00:35:43.290
So that's the Rus'.

00:35:43.290 --> 00:35:44.790
So what do we know about them?

00:35:46.110 --> 00:35:49.830
As I said, they're seeking
a trade route south.

00:35:49.830 --> 00:35:51.450
The first mention we have of them

00:35:51.450 --> 00:35:52.440
in our part of the world

00:35:52.440 --> 00:35:56.220
is in the 840s, 850s, 860s.

00:35:56.220 --> 00:35:58.080
They're mentioned as Scandinavians

00:35:58.080 --> 00:35:59.700
engaged in the slave trade

00:35:59.700 --> 00:36:01.590
in order to gain silver.

00:36:01.590 --> 00:36:03.570
As I mentioned before, we
have these silver hoards,

00:36:03.570 --> 00:36:06.379
which is part of the evidence

00:36:06.379 --> 00:36:07.629
for what they were doing.

00:36:08.790 --> 00:36:11.160
They are still nomads, right?

00:36:11.160 --> 00:36:12.240
They're marine nomads.

00:36:12.240 --> 00:36:14.670
They move mainly by
sea, but they're nomads.

00:36:14.670 --> 00:36:17.733
And one of the big
underlying transitions here,

00:36:18.893 --> 00:36:20.793
I've emphasized it in terms of slavery

00:36:22.744 --> 00:36:24.330
versus peasantry, right?

00:36:24.330 --> 00:36:25.500
But another way to think about this

00:36:25.500 --> 00:36:28.680
is nomadism versus settlement.

00:36:28.680 --> 00:36:31.020
When the people in power are still moving,

00:36:31.020 --> 00:36:32.460
that's one situation.

00:36:32.460 --> 00:36:34.290
When the people in power settle

00:36:34.290 --> 00:36:36.570
and build cities, or take
over someone else's cities,

00:36:36.570 --> 00:36:38.070
that's a different situation.

00:36:38.070 --> 00:36:40.620
So what the Vikings did

00:36:40.620 --> 00:36:44.280
was they overwhelmed
sedentary civilizations.

00:36:44.280 --> 00:36:45.960
They took cities.

00:36:45.960 --> 00:36:48.180
They negotiated trade
terms, which is what you do.

00:36:48.180 --> 00:36:49.593
That's just normal.

00:36:50.820 --> 00:36:53.760
What's special is that they
end up settling in Kyiv,

00:36:53.760 --> 00:36:55.620
and that's when we get a state,

00:36:55.620 --> 00:36:56.850
and I'll talk about that.

00:36:56.850 --> 00:36:59.040
So as I mentioned, they tried

00:36:59.040 --> 00:37:00.720
to go down the Volga River,

00:37:00.720 --> 00:37:01.950
which is in the middle of Russia.

00:37:01.950 --> 00:37:04.710
They were blocked by the Bulgars,

00:37:04.710 --> 00:37:05.760
the Muslim Bulgars.

00:37:05.760 --> 00:37:08.160
And then they went down the Dnipro.

00:37:08.160 --> 00:37:09.270
And went down the Dnipro,

00:37:09.270 --> 00:37:12.270
then we're setting up
the history where we are.

00:37:12.270 --> 00:37:15.360
The people who dominated Kyiv and Ukraine

00:37:15.360 --> 00:37:18.300
at the time were the Khazars.

00:37:18.300 --> 00:37:20.760
The Khazars are tough to figure out.

00:37:20.760 --> 00:37:22.920
We have no written documents at all

00:37:22.920 --> 00:37:25.650
that are directly from their state.

00:37:25.650 --> 00:37:29.400
It was a multiethnic and
multi-confessional realm,

00:37:29.400 --> 00:37:31.320
which had some Christians and some Jews

00:37:31.320 --> 00:37:34.794
and some Muslims in it, but also had lots

00:37:34.794 --> 00:37:37.590
of non-monotheistic believers

00:37:37.590 --> 00:37:39.930
in it as well.

00:37:39.930 --> 00:37:42.270
The Khazars came to an end in a way

00:37:42.270 --> 00:37:45.540
which is also incredibly confusing.

00:37:45.540 --> 00:37:47.760
There was rivalry among
the various monotheisms

00:37:47.760 --> 00:37:49.980
about which monotheism
they all converted to.

00:37:49.980 --> 00:37:52.470
And it's actually not clear
they converted to any of them.

00:37:52.470 --> 00:37:53.790
There's a beautiful novel, though,

00:37:53.790 --> 00:37:55.620
about this called "The
Dictionary of the Khazars"

00:37:55.620 --> 00:37:57.813
by a Croatian writer called Pavic,

00:37:59.837 --> 00:38:00.937
which I don't know if you like read

00:38:00.937 --> 00:38:02.730
"Choose Your Own Adventure"
stories as a kid,

00:38:02.730 --> 00:38:04.770
but it's like, it's a novel,

00:38:04.770 --> 00:38:06.450
which is set up as three dictionaries,

00:38:06.450 --> 00:38:07.510
a Christian, a Jewish

00:38:08.358 --> 00:38:10.320
and a Muslim, where you kind of choose

00:38:10.320 --> 00:38:12.390
like in what order you read it.

00:38:12.390 --> 00:38:13.410
It's very beautiful.

00:38:13.410 --> 00:38:15.630
But it gets across the
kind of lack of narrative

00:38:15.630 --> 00:38:17.190
that we actually have about the Khazars.

00:38:17.190 --> 00:38:18.723
We have very little.

00:38:20.730 --> 00:38:22.740
Oh, Cyril visited them.

00:38:22.740 --> 00:38:23.730
That's interesting,

00:38:23.730 --> 00:38:26.700
Cyril, our same Cyril who went to Moravia,

00:38:26.700 --> 00:38:30.300
also visited Khazaria in 860,

00:38:30.300 --> 00:38:32.580
in order to try to spread Christianity.

00:38:32.580 --> 00:38:36.960
So we know that they weakened

00:38:36.960 --> 00:38:39.720
and we know that they faded into,

00:38:39.720 --> 00:38:43.020
married into the Rus' in some way.

00:38:43.020 --> 00:38:45.750
We know this partly because of language.

00:38:45.750 --> 00:38:47.760
When the Rus' settle down and start

00:38:47.760 --> 00:38:49.023
to try to rule Kyiv,

00:38:50.092 --> 00:38:52.773
they called their leader a khagan,

00:38:53.998 --> 00:38:55.380
and that's a Turkic word, right?

00:38:55.380 --> 00:38:57.630
That's a word that they
got from the Khazars.

00:38:58.835 --> 00:39:01.110
Their ruler is first called a khagan.

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:01.943
Okay.

00:39:03.832 --> 00:39:07.290
So the Rus' are settling into Kyiv,

00:39:07.290 --> 00:39:10.140
late 800s, early 900s.

00:39:10.140 --> 00:39:12.003
We know they dominate Podil.

00:39:14.310 --> 00:39:17.073
That's the part of Kyiv
from which you would trade.

00:39:19.380 --> 00:39:21.397
We know they dominate, they control Kyiv

00:39:22.470 --> 00:39:25.230
by about the year 900.

00:39:25.230 --> 00:39:28.410
They're basically taking over
what the Khazars left them.

00:39:28.410 --> 00:39:30.000
They're taking tribute from the people

00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:32.610
who used to be paying the Khazars tribute.

00:39:32.610 --> 00:39:34.050
That's a sign of who's in charge

00:39:34.050 --> 00:39:36.090
that historians can follow pretty well,

00:39:36.090 --> 00:39:37.410
is who's getting the tribute, right?

00:39:37.410 --> 00:39:40.233
Who can make other people
regularly pay money.

00:39:41.533 --> 00:39:45.660
By 911, a ruler of the Rus', called Oleg,

00:39:45.660 --> 00:39:48.510
is signing a treaty with Byzantium, right?

00:39:48.510 --> 00:39:50.640
They're reaching Byzantium,
but not with violence.

00:39:50.640 --> 00:39:53.250
They're now reaching
Byzantium with diplomacy.

00:39:53.250 --> 00:39:55.320
But you can tell that they're still,

00:39:55.320 --> 00:39:56.340
they're not just traders.

00:39:56.340 --> 00:39:57.840
They're people who are feared.

00:39:59.215 --> 00:40:01.080
A provision of this treaty with Byzantium

00:40:01.080 --> 00:40:03.750
is that the Rus' are only
allowed to go through

00:40:03.750 --> 00:40:05.820
one gate of the city, a specified gate,

00:40:05.820 --> 00:40:08.160
and they can't come in more
than 50 at a time, right?

00:40:08.160 --> 00:40:10.140
So there's a sense that
perhaps these people,

00:40:10.140 --> 00:40:11.940
you know, might cause a
certain amount of trouble

00:40:11.940 --> 00:40:14.640
if you just let them
come in in large numbers.

00:40:14.640 --> 00:40:15.473
Okay.

00:40:16.800 --> 00:40:19.080
To put this back into perspective,

00:40:19.080 --> 00:40:20.700
we're getting towards the year 1000.

00:40:20.700 --> 00:40:22.470
I'm gonna deliver the promised conversion

00:40:22.470 --> 00:40:24.270
of Volodymyr before this is all over.

00:40:24.270 --> 00:40:26.460
But I want you to notice that in this time

00:40:26.460 --> 00:40:28.530
in the 900s, the 10th century,

00:40:28.530 --> 00:40:31.680
this is the time of a lot of
other conversions as well.

00:40:31.680 --> 00:40:32.860
This is the time

00:40:35.096 --> 00:40:36.990
when the Vikings in Scandinavia

00:40:36.990 --> 00:40:39.120
are starting to move towards establishing

00:40:39.120 --> 00:40:42.480
the Danish and the Swedish
and the Norwegian states,

00:40:42.480 --> 00:40:43.870
which are also associated

00:40:45.330 --> 00:40:47.013
with Christian conversions.

00:40:49.260 --> 00:40:50.670
The 10th century is a time

00:40:50.670 --> 00:40:52.440
when the Vikings are settling down

00:40:52.440 --> 00:40:55.170
and founding states everywhere,

00:40:55.170 --> 00:40:56.430
including in continental Europe.

00:40:56.430 --> 00:40:58.680
So in 911, the same year of this treaty,

00:40:58.680 --> 00:41:01.650
is when Charles the Simple of France

00:41:01.650 --> 00:41:04.170
grants Duke Rollo, who's a descendant

00:41:04.170 --> 00:41:06.690
of the Vikings, Normandy.

00:41:06.690 --> 00:41:07.860
Normandy being Northern France.

00:41:07.860 --> 00:41:09.420
Normandy also being the launching point

00:41:09.420 --> 00:41:12.180
for the Normans, who then
control Great Britain.

00:41:12.180 --> 00:41:14.280
So this is a time of Viking conversion,

00:41:14.280 --> 00:41:16.620
a time of Viking state creation.

00:41:16.620 --> 00:41:19.110
Our story is special
because it's taking place

00:41:19.110 --> 00:41:20.880
amidst different kinds of people,

00:41:20.880 --> 00:41:22.200
amidst the Khazars.

00:41:22.200 --> 00:41:24.420
It's taking place with
different kinds of models,

00:41:24.420 --> 00:41:25.650
the Slavic models.

00:41:25.650 --> 00:41:27.540
And fundamentally,
because it's taking place

00:41:27.540 --> 00:41:29.070
at a time when there was a choice

00:41:29.070 --> 00:41:32.490
between two different
versions of Christianity.

00:41:32.490 --> 00:41:34.053
The first time. Okay.

00:41:34.950 --> 00:41:36.093
When you convert.

00:41:37.130 --> 00:41:39.543
The story always goes, you convert.

00:41:40.380 --> 00:41:41.910
You believe it.

00:41:41.910 --> 00:41:43.170
All of your people convert.

00:41:43.170 --> 00:41:45.300
It's like everything (snaps
fingers) changes all at once.

00:41:45.300 --> 00:41:47.220
That's not how it happens.

00:41:47.220 --> 00:41:51.420
Olga, who rules from 945 to 962,

00:41:51.420 --> 00:41:54.210
does convert, but her kids don't convert

00:41:54.210 --> 00:41:55.800
and her grandchildren don't convert,

00:41:55.800 --> 00:41:57.810
and her people don't really convert.

00:41:57.810 --> 00:42:00.453
She converts to Eastern Christianity,

00:42:01.320 --> 00:42:03.270
but then she asks for
some German missionaries

00:42:03.270 --> 00:42:05.790
to come a couple of years later.

00:42:05.790 --> 00:42:09.510
Her son, Sviatoslav,
which is a great name,

00:42:09.510 --> 00:42:12.003
still borne by many lovable people.

00:42:12.840 --> 00:42:17.100
Sviatoslav rules from 962 to 972.

00:42:17.100 --> 00:42:18.210
He's a pagan.

00:42:18.210 --> 00:42:19.290
Her kid is a pagan.

00:42:19.290 --> 00:42:20.970
We have few sources about why,

00:42:20.970 --> 00:42:23.130
but I really like one of them,

00:42:23.130 --> 00:42:24.810
where he basically says,

00:42:24.810 --> 00:42:27.135
he's asked why he can't
convert to Christianity,

00:42:27.135 --> 00:42:28.237
and he says, "Well, like my crew

00:42:28.237 --> 00:42:31.015
"would all make fun of me." (laughs)

00:42:31.015 --> 00:42:33.061
(students laugh)

00:42:33.061 --> 00:42:34.890
And that is kind of what Sviatoslav did.

00:42:34.890 --> 00:42:36.900
He, in the 960s,

00:42:36.900 --> 00:42:38.760
he seems to have destroyed the remnants

00:42:38.760 --> 00:42:40.050
of the Khazar state.

00:42:40.050 --> 00:42:42.360
And then in the late 960s, early 970s,

00:42:42.360 --> 00:42:44.010
he campaigned in the Balkans

00:42:44.010 --> 00:42:48.870
to try to gain control of
the Balkans, and failed.

00:42:48.870 --> 00:42:49.890
When he was leaving,

00:42:49.890 --> 00:42:51.690
this is one of the reasons
we know he was a pagan,

00:42:51.690 --> 00:42:54.150
in 971, he invoked

00:42:54.150 --> 00:42:56.970
two Slavic pagan gods, Perun,

00:42:56.970 --> 00:43:00.060
who's the god of thunder, and Veles,

00:43:00.060 --> 00:43:02.610
who is the god of the
earth and of the harvest.

00:43:02.610 --> 00:43:05.310
And by the way, in the Slavic mythology,

00:43:05.310 --> 00:43:06.960
which is kind of like the Scandinavians

00:43:06.960 --> 00:43:08.460
are clearly influencing it.

00:43:08.460 --> 00:43:10.667
But in the Slavic
mythology, Perun and Veles

00:43:10.667 --> 00:43:12.330
are in this kind of embrace,

00:43:12.330 --> 00:43:15.424
where you explain the
change of the seasons

00:43:15.424 --> 00:43:16.950
by battles between the sky,

00:43:16.950 --> 00:43:19.620
which is Perun, and the
earth, which is Veles.

00:43:19.620 --> 00:43:22.053
It's actually kind of beautiful. Okay.

00:43:23.490 --> 00:43:25.950
So in 972, on his way back,

00:43:25.950 --> 00:43:27.750
Sviatoslav is killed

00:43:27.750 --> 00:43:31.530
on the Dnipro by Pechenegs,

00:43:31.530 --> 00:43:33.240
who make a cup from his skull,

00:43:33.240 --> 00:43:35.013
as one did in the time and place.

00:43:37.410 --> 00:43:40.200
So that leaves us open.

00:43:40.200 --> 00:43:43.170
There's then a very complicated
succession struggle,

00:43:43.170 --> 00:43:44.790
at the end of which

00:43:44.790 --> 00:43:48.120
the person who comes
to power is Volodymyr,

00:43:48.120 --> 00:43:49.980
who's remembered as Volodymyr the Great,

00:43:49.980 --> 00:43:52.770
who is the person who actually converts.

