that makes them seem plausible,

00:44:14.010 --> 00:44:15.150
but it's kind of more revealing

00:44:15.150 --> 00:44:16.560
about how things look in retrospect,

00:44:16.560 --> 00:44:17.580
but it's still fun to read.

00:44:17.580 --> 00:44:18.413
Okay.

00:44:18.413 --> 00:44:22.560
So this is about how you make
a choice for Christianity,

00:44:22.560 --> 00:44:25.290
and it aestheticizes it and
makes it all very clear.

00:44:25.290 --> 00:44:28.350
The Bulgars, means the Muslims, right?

00:44:28.350 --> 00:44:29.940
The Bulgars bow down and sit

00:44:29.940 --> 00:44:31.080
and look hither and dither,

00:44:31.080 --> 00:44:32.370
and there is no joy among them,

00:44:32.370 --> 00:44:34.260
but only a dreadful stench.

00:44:34.260 --> 00:44:36.540
Their religion is not good.

00:44:36.540 --> 00:44:38.310
Then we went to the Germans,

00:44:38.310 --> 00:44:40.140
the Western Christians, the Franks.

00:44:40.140 --> 00:44:41.760
Then we went to the
Germans, and we saw them

00:44:41.760 --> 00:44:43.950
celebrating many services
in their churches,

00:44:43.950 --> 00:44:45.960
but we saw no beauty there, right?

00:44:45.960 --> 00:44:48.510
Eternal complaint about
Germans and their churches.

00:44:50.537 --> 00:44:52.050
Then we went to the
Greeks, the Byzantines.

00:44:52.050 --> 00:44:53.250
Then we went to the Greeks,

00:44:53.250 --> 00:44:55.230
and they led us to the place
where they worship God,

00:44:55.230 --> 00:44:56.810
and we knew not whether we
were on heaven or Earth, right?

00:44:56.810 --> 00:44:57.930
So it's all very clear.

00:44:57.930 --> 00:44:59.580
It's all very aestheticized.

00:44:59.580 --> 00:45:01.290
But having gotten this far in the class,

00:45:01.290 --> 00:45:04.011
you know that it has to
do with other things.

00:45:04.011 --> 00:45:05.220
It's gonna have to do with power.

00:45:05.220 --> 00:45:06.120
It's gonna have to do with the choices

00:45:06.120 --> 00:45:07.950
of a particular ruler.

00:45:07.950 --> 00:45:11.373
Volodymyr himself, no particular
religious preferences.

00:45:12.311 --> 00:45:14.820
Maybe flirted with Islam
at one stage in his life.

00:45:14.820 --> 00:45:18.000
Certainly tolerant of,
encouraging of pagan worship

00:45:18.000 --> 00:45:21.810
in Kyiv when he took power in Kyiv in 980.

00:45:21.810 --> 00:45:25.050
We know that Perun, the god
of thunder, was worshiped.

00:45:25.050 --> 00:45:27.660
What he had was an opportunity,

00:45:27.660 --> 00:45:28.980
and he took it.

00:45:28.980 --> 00:45:30.690
The great power in the south,

00:45:30.690 --> 00:45:33.423
the Byzantines, were in internal turmoil.

00:45:36.303 --> 00:45:38.310
There was a rebel who sought to take power

00:45:38.310 --> 00:45:39.780
from the Byzantine emperor,

00:45:39.780 --> 00:45:41.760
and Volodymyr threw the power of Rus'

00:45:41.760 --> 00:45:43.810
on the side of the Byzantine emperor

00:45:44.760 --> 00:45:48.270
and helped to win, helped
the Byzantine emperor

00:45:48.270 --> 00:45:50.850
to preserve power in a campaign in,

00:45:50.850 --> 00:45:52.233
you guessed it, Crimea.

00:45:53.310 --> 00:45:56.857
So Volodymyr, having done this, then says,

00:45:56.857 --> 00:45:58.867
"I would now like to marry

00:45:58.867 --> 00:46:00.030
"the sister of the emperor,"

00:46:00.030 --> 00:46:02.310
which is a big ask, but the circumstances

00:46:02.310 --> 00:46:03.310
were what they were.

00:46:04.162 --> 00:46:06.907
And the Byzantines
answered, not surprisingly,

00:46:06.907 --> 00:46:09.097
"Yes, but there's a little proviso,

00:46:09.097 --> 00:46:11.853
"which is that you must
convert to Christianity," okay?

00:46:14.790 --> 00:46:16.560
It's a little power play,

00:46:16.560 --> 00:46:18.960
the Rus' helped the Byzantine ruler,

00:46:18.960 --> 00:46:20.550
but then there's the larger power play,

00:46:20.550 --> 00:46:22.500
which is happening all
over Eastern Europe,

00:46:22.500 --> 00:46:25.350
which is that one or the
other of these large states

00:46:25.350 --> 00:46:26.670
is eventually gonna get you to convert

00:46:26.670 --> 00:46:28.530
to its version of Christianity.

00:46:28.530 --> 00:46:31.740
This time, the conversion sticks.

00:46:31.740 --> 00:46:33.180
There's a permanent link now

00:46:33.180 --> 00:46:35.760
between Byzantium and Rus'.

00:46:35.760 --> 00:46:38.520
Rus' soldiers remain in Constantinople

00:46:38.520 --> 00:46:40.560
as an imperial guard.

00:46:40.560 --> 00:46:41.790
The Byzantine emperor

00:46:41.790 --> 00:46:45.570
sends Greek-speaking churchman to Kyiv.

00:46:45.570 --> 00:46:48.090
Churches are built, most
famously Saint Sophia,

00:46:48.090 --> 00:46:50.820
which still stands in the center of Kyiv,

00:46:50.820 --> 00:46:52.260
in all of its beauty.

00:46:52.260 --> 00:46:55.680
Volodymyr ensures that the
population of Kyiv converts.

00:46:55.680 --> 00:46:58.140
Idols and temples that
he himself had raised,

00:46:58.140 --> 00:46:59.670
or allowed to be built, he destroys,

00:46:59.670 --> 00:47:02.880
has thrown into the river.

00:47:02.880 --> 00:47:03.903
And as a result,

00:47:05.520 --> 00:47:07.800
Rus' becomes part of the Byzantine world,

00:47:07.800 --> 00:47:10.350
and in a couple of ways,

00:47:10.350 --> 00:47:13.230
part of the classical world.

00:47:13.230 --> 00:47:15.150
One way is continuity.

00:47:15.150 --> 00:47:17.790
The continuity of Greece, Rome,

00:47:17.790 --> 00:47:20.277
Byzantium and Rus'.

00:47:23.012 --> 00:47:24.720
That's one way.

00:47:24.720 --> 00:47:26.340
But the other way

00:47:26.340 --> 00:47:29.310
is that Rus' is now going

00:47:29.310 --> 00:47:33.033
to extend territorially northwards,

00:47:33.930 --> 00:47:35.130
this classical civilization,

00:47:35.130 --> 00:47:36.720
which had never gotten so far north.

00:47:36.720 --> 00:47:39.420
Which is, it's a big part of the history

00:47:39.420 --> 00:47:41.760
of the Slavs in general, of
Eastern Europe in general,

00:47:41.760 --> 00:47:44.100
is that, sure, there are these models

00:47:44.100 --> 00:47:45.420
that come from the south,

00:47:45.420 --> 00:47:47.730
and now they are going further north,

00:47:47.730 --> 00:47:49.440
which brings me to Serhii Plokhy.

